articles.author: Lee Ying Shan
articles.title: Asia-Pacific markets open lower after strong U.S. jobs report clouds Fed rate-cut path - CNBC
articles.description: China's December exports rose 10.7% from a year earlier, beating Reuters' expectations of a 7.3% year-on-year growth. Imports  unexpectedly rose 1%.
articles.content:
Asia-Pacific markets traded lower Monday, after U.S. jobs report on Friday dampened investors' hopes for early interest rate cuts by the Federal Reserve.
